import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="region", y="income", data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel("Region")
    ax.set_ylabel("Income")
    ax.set_title("What is the distribution of income across different regions?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="group", y="income", data=data, ci=None, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Income Group', ylabel='Average Income')
    plt.title('What is the average income for each income group?', wrap=True)
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.2f'), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha = 'center', va = 'center', xytext = (0, 10), textcoords = 'offset points')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    income_by_region = data.groupby('region')['total'].sum().reset_index()
    income_by_region['pct'] = income_by_region['total'] / income_by_region['total'].sum() * 100
    plt.pie(income_by_region['pct'], labels=income_by_region['region'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.legend(title='Regions', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    plt.axis('equal')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.title('What is the percentage of total income generated by each region?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
